							<h2 class="h2_sub_title_v1">Social Insurance</h2>

							<ul class="summary_list_wrap mg_t5">
								<li class="text_type_v11">When married immigrant women with Korean nationality gain employment, they are automatically signed up for social insurance programs (national pension, health insurance, employment insurance).</li>
								<li class="text_type_v11">Married immigrant women without Korean nationality may choose whether or not they wish to apply for social insurance, but are generally encouraged to do so.</li>
								<li class="text_type_v11">Insurance fees are deducted from the worker's salary and transferred to the Korean Institute for Social Insurance.</li>
							</ul>
						</section>
